Detailed Description

cvmx_pow_qos_rnd#

Contains the round definitions for issuing new work. Each round consists of 8 bits with each bit corresponding to a QOS level. There are 4 rounds contained in each register for a total of 32 rounds. The issue logic traverses through the rounds sequentially (lowest round to highest round) in an attempt to find new work for each PP. Within each round, the issue logic traverses through the QOS levels sequentially (highest QOS to lowest QOS) skipping over each QOS level with a clear bit in the round mask. Note: setting a QOS level to all zeroes in all issue round registers will prevent work from being issued from that QOS level.
